.TH "devm_backlight_device_register" 9 "devm_backlight_device_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_backlight_device_register \- register a new backlight device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct backlight_device *" devm_backlight_device_register
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "struct device *parent "  ","
.BI "void *devdata "  ","
.BI "const struct backlight_ops *ops "  ","
.BI "const struct backlight_properties *props "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the device to register
.IP "name" 12
the name of the device
.IP "parent" 12
a pointer to the parent device (often the same as \fIdev\fP)
.IP "devdata" 12
an optional pointer to be stored for private driver use
.IP "ops" 12
the backlight operations structure
.IP "props" 12
the backlight properties
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Creates and registers new backlight device. When a backlight device
is registered the configuration must be specified in the \fIprops\fP
parameter. See description of \fIbacklight_properties\fP.

struct backlight on success, or an ERR_PTR on error
.SH "RETURN"
